OL,6,FA gynaecologist who removed two
OL,7,Fpatients' ovaries without consent at
OL,8,FGuernsey's Princess Elizabeth Hospital
OL,9,Fhas been deemed 'fit to practice' by a
OL,10,Fmedical tribunal.
OL,12,FDr Ali Shokouh-Amiri faced more than
OL,13,F100 allegations of inappropriate
OL,14,Fbehaviour with 24 instances proven but
OL,15,Fthe Medical Practitioners Tribunal
OL,16,FService ruled that he has "shown good
OL,17,Finsight into his failures ... and put
OL,18,Fin place procedures and actions to
OL,19,Faddress his failings to ensure they do
OL,20,Fnot happen again".
