OL,6,FIn a written judgment, the Tribunal
OL,7,Fexplained: "Dr Shokouh-Amiri's
OL,8,Fmisconduct was serious and had the
OL,9,Fpotential to affect the public's
OL,10,Fconfidence in the profession.
OL,12,F"However, the Tribunal reminded itself
OL,13,Fof the significant level of insight,
OL,14,Fremorse and remediation demonstrated
OL,15,Fby Dr Shokouh-Amiri and his acceptance
OL,16,Fof responsibility from the outset of
OL,17,Fthe regulatory process and admissions
OL,18,Fat this hearing. He fully engaged and
OL,19,Fparticipated with the GMC (General
OL,20,FMedical Council) procedures since the
OL,21,Fstart.
